[SN]TITLE[SN]
Shakespeare 'gets to the big stuff really quickly'

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
It's 400 years since the Shakespeare's death and his writings are still as popular as ever.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
22 April 2016 Last updated at 07:01 BST
Shakespeare expert Michael Rosen tells Leah why his plays are still so interesting - he tackles the big stuff like love, death, greed and hate!
We also learn all about the sayings and words we use today that he might well have been responsible for.
